	model to the pore-scale simulation of the spread of a nonreactive
	solute. We then simulate the reactive case for different flow rates
	and compute the product formed by the reaction. We investigate whether
	use of the transverse dispersion coeiffcient gives the proper degree
	of mixing to accurately simulate the amount of product formed in
	the system. The results are compared with available experimental
	evidence and theoretical findings. Our results indicate that transverse
	dispersion coefficients that describe spreading of nonreactive solutes
	also may be used to model transverse mixing and reaction.},
