	In networks of equal sized pores, TW behavior occurs, and concentration
	distributions can be predicted by an analytical solution. For increasing
	physical heterogeneity the balance between the dispersive and adsorptive
	forces remains absent because the second central moment continues
	to grow as a function of time. The growth rate of this moment is
	a function of pore-scale heterogeneity.},
